hooks/ceph_hooks.py.message:
docstring with purpose, params/types.

BUT, there is also a significant error in the default param for data:

Python passes by reference for all but the simplest types; thus normally when a dictionary is passed in, it's the same dict as the caller passed to called function.  However, with a default value, the "data" param here gets bound to a once-only initialised default dictionary.  If data is then changed in the body of the function, that gets retained until the next time the function is called without the data param.  i.e. it is persistent.  This is an annoying class of errors, and the typical way of handling it is:

    def _function(data=None):
        if data is None:
            data = {}
        ...
